creator: Various
description:
LibriVox recording of Short Poetry Collection 124 by Various.
Read in English by volunteer readers

This is a collection of poems read by LibriVox volunteers for September 2013. This collection includes the following:
Autumn (To My Mother) by Jean Starr Untermeyer
Awakening by George William Russell
By the Margin of the Deep by George William Russell
The Death of Autumn by Edna St. Vincent Millay
Fairies by Rose Fyleman
Fifty Years Spent by Maxwell Struthers Burt
Harbury by Louise Driscoll
If by e. e. cummings
The Lark Ascending by George Meredith
The Law of the Jungle by Rudyard Kipling
Men Improve with the Years by William Butler Yeats
Mr. Apollinax by T. S. Eliot
A Musical Instrument by Elizabeth Barrett Browning
The Path that Leads to Nowhere by Corinne Roosevelt Robinson
Quatrains from Omar Khayyám by Omar Khayyám, translated by Edwin Kendall Cutter
Sonnet XLIII by Elizabeth Barrett Browning
The Statue by Ella Wheeler Wilcox
There Is a Garden in Her Face by Thomas Campion
Untitled by Marion Dix Mosher
The Wants of Man by John Quincy Adams

For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording.

For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org.
